description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join a friendly, dynamic and forward thinking practice with an Outstanding CQC rating, in the Berkshire town of Reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is full-time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an additional competent Paramedic Practitioner to join our duty team, who is looking to use their skills in a General Practice setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are already an experienced Paramedic able to deal with the challenges of the role and looking for a change of environment. We can offer you variety of work, fulfilling patient focused care, more family friendly hours and career progression within a supportive multi-disciplinary team structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be HCPC registered and hold one of the following qualifications BTECH Level 4, BSc, DipHE, FdSc or have acheived the IHCD Paramedic Award.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Urgent care centre (UCC) experience or primary care experience is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would be advantageous to have completed modules in the following: Minor Illness, Minor injuries, Drugs and therapeutics, Clinicial thinking and reasoning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role would suit candidiates interested in new and innovative ways of providing primary care and who are keen to work in a large supported, multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About us - we are a large practice serving 30,000 patients+ in Reading and have championed an allied healthcare professional team which currently comprises 18 GPs, 4 clinical pharmacists,1 physicians associate, 3 prescribing nurses, 4 nurses, 4 paramedics, 3 HCAs and 2 social prescribers. We have mentors and trainers in the practice and you will be supported by a large, enthusiastic and visionary clinical team.&lt;/p&gt;
